{
  "text": "Aldehyde Dehydrogenase (ALDH), a drug-resistance gene found in normal hematopoietic stem cells [CITATION_1] , was recently found in several types of cancer initiating cells, including NSCLC [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Expression of ALDH is regulated by the Hh pathway [CITATION_4] and blockade of hedgehog signaling inhibits pancreatic cancer invasion and metastases [CITATION_5] . ALDH1 participates in the oxidation of retinal to all-trans retinoic acid [CITATION_6] , and confers drug resistance to chemotherapeutic agents, such as cyclophosphamide, by an uncertain mechanism [CITATION_7] .",
